column2: We imported all of the microarray data files into R and normalized them simultaneously. The normalization procedure consists of two steps executed with programs in the Bioconductor package GCRMA. First, we compute the probe affinities using the annotation file hgu133plus2cdf. Second, we normalize the data by setting two options and leaving the rest at default values. The affinity.info option is set to use the probe affinities computed in the first step. The type option is set to fullmodel which uses both the sequence information and mismatch probe model.
